On one TF (SOLUSDT / BTCUSDT 15m or 1H):
1) ≥3 touches of the same support zone;
2) ≥3 lower highs;
3) compression usually 12–30+ candles — not a 3-candle sketch.

Intraday crypto: check BTC first — a strong bitcoin pump weakens alt shorts.

Valid only if recorded BEFORE the first transaction:
• max. 1 additive;
• total loss ≤ −1.5R from the original risk;
• Cancellation level - exit for everyone.

There is no log entry before entry - averaging is prohibited. The alternative is always: stop −1R and a new idea tomorrow.

Head and shoulders is a bullish-to-bearish reversal:
1) left shoulder (peak);
2) pullback to the “neck”;
3) head — a higher peak;
4) pullback to the neck again;
5) right shoulder ≈ left shoulder height;
6) close below the neckline.

The neckline joins the two troughs between peaks; a mild slope is fine.

Inverse head and shoulders is a bullish reversal:
• left shoulder (trough);
• rally to the neck;
• head — a deeper trough;
• back to the neck;
• right shoulder ≈ left;
• close above the neckline.

The neck joins the peaks between the troughs.

Do not open a trade if:
• important news / FOMC / CPI in the coming minutes;
• ATR “storm” - candles at 2–3x normal, stop does not interfere with the risk%;
• BTC is strongly against your alt idea;
• price in the middle of the range without an edge;
• the daily loss limit has already been taken.

One red flag = pause. Not “I’ll take a little risk.”
